name: Sunyshore City Gym
text: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play. If another card with the same name is in play, you can't play this card.

Any damage done by attacks from Lightning Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) to the Defending Pokémon isn't affected by Resistance. Each Lightning Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) has no Weakness.

name: Team Galactic's Invention G-107 Technical Machine
text: Attach this card to 1 of your Pokémon SP in play. That Pokémon may use this card's attack instead of its own. When the Pokémon this card is attached to is no longer a Pokémon SP, discard this card.

name: Team Galactic's Invention G-109 SP Radar
text: Choose a card from your hand and put it on top of your deck. Search your deck for a Pokémon SP, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. (If this is the only card in your hand, you can't play this card.)

name: Underground Expedition
text: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Look at the 4 cards from the bottom of your deck. Choose any 2 cards you find there and put them into your hand. Put the remaining cards back on the bottom of your deck in any order.

name: Volkner's Philosophy
text: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
You may discard a card from your hand. Then, draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. (If you can't draw any cards, you can't play this card.)

name: Darkness Energy
text: If the Pokémon Darkness Energy is attached to attacks, the attack does 10 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance). Ignore this effect if the Pokémon that Darkness Energy is attached to isn't Darkness. Darkness Energy provides Darkness Energy. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.)

name: Metal Energy
text: Damage done by attacks to the Pokémon that Metal Energy is attached to is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance). Ignore this effect if the Pokémon that Metal Energy is attached to isn't Metal. Metal Energy provides Metal Energy. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.)

name: SP Energy
text: SP Energy provides Colorless Energy. If the Pokémon SP Energy is attached to is a Pokémon SP, SP Energy provides every type of Energy but provides only 1 Energy at a time. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.)

name: Upper Energy
text: Upper Energy provides Colorless Energy. If you have more Prize cards left than your opponent and this card is attached to a Pokémon (excluding Pokémon LV.X), Upper Energy provides Colorless Colorless Energy.

name: Alakazam 4

ability.name: Damage Switch
ability.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokémon SP to another of your Pokémon SP. This power can't be used if Alakazam 4 is affected by a Special Condition.

text: Put this card onto your Active Alakazam 4. Alakazam 4 LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous Level.

attacks.name: Mind Shock
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Floatzel GL

ability.name: Water Rescue
ability.text: Whenever any of your Water Pokémon (excluding any Floatzel GL) is Knocked Out by damage from your opponent's attack, you may put that Pokémon and all cards that were attached to it from your discard pile into your hand.

text: Put this card onto your Active Floatzel GL. Floatzel GL LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous Level.

attacks.name: Energy Cyclone
attacks.text: Choose as many Energy cards from your hand as you like and show them to your opponent. This attack does 20 damage times the number of Energy cards you chose. Put those Energy cards on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Flygon

ability.name: Wind Erosion
ability.text: As long as Flygon is your Active Pokémon, discard the top card from your opponent's deck between turns.

text: Put this card onto your Active Flygon. Flygon LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous Level.

attacks.name: Extreme Attack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon LV.X. This attack does 150 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Gallade 4

ability.name: Blade Storm
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Gallade 4 LV.X from your hand onto your Active Gallade 4, you may put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon.

text: Put this card onto your Active Gallade 4. Gallade 4 LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous Level.

attacks.name: Aimed Cut
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on the Defending Pokémon.

name: Hippowdon

ability.name: Sand Reset
ability.text: Once during a game on your turn (before your attack), each player shuffles all cards in play (excluding Pokémon and Supporter cards) into his or her deck. You can't use more than 1 Sand Reset Poké-Power each game.

text: Put this card onto your Active Hippowdon. Hippowdon LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous Level.

attacks.name: Double Shoot
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fighting Energy attached to Hippowdon and choose 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to each of them. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Infernape 4

ability.name: Intimidating Roar
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may have your opponent switch his or her Active Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon. This power can't be used if Infernape 4 is affected by a Special Condition.

text: Put this card onto your Active Infernape 4. Infernape 4 LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous Level.

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy attached to Infernape 4.

name: Luxray GL

ability.name: Bright Look
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Luxray GL LV.X from your hand onto your Active Luxray GL, you may switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

text: Put this card onto your Active Luxray GL. Luxray GL LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous Level.

attacks.name: Flash Impact
attacks.text: Does 30 damage to 1 of your Pokémon, and don't apply Weakness and Resistance to this damage.

name: Mismagius GL

ability.name: Magical Return
ability.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may return a Pokémon Tool card or Technical Machine card attached to your Pokémon to your hand. This power can't be used if Mismagius GL is affected by a Special Condition.

text: Put this card onto your Active Mismagius GL. Mismagius GL LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous Level.

attacks.name: Darkness Magic
attacks.text: Count the number of cards in your hand. Put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokémon. You can't put more than 8 damage counters in this way.

name: Snorlax

ability.name: Big Appetite
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Snorlax is your Active Pokémon, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. If you do, Snorlax is now Asleep. This power can't be used if Snorlax is affected by a Special Condition.

text: Put this card onto your Active Snorlax. Snorlax LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous Level.

attacks.name: Exercise
attacks.text: You may discard as many Energy cards as you like from your hand. If you do, remove that many damage counters from Snorlax.

attacks.name: Thunder Jolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Pikachu does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Fly
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Flying Pikachu during your opponent's next turn.

ability.name: Fan Shift
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Fan Rotom's type is Colorless until the end of your turn.

attacks.name: Spin Storm
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent returns the Defending Pokémon and all cards attached to it to his or her hand.

attacks.name: Air Slash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard an Energy attached to Fan Rotom.

ability.name: Frost Shift
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Frost Rotom's type is Water until the end of your turn.

attacks.name: Hail
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Crushing Ice
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Colorless Energy in the Defending Pokémon's Retreat Cost (after applying effects to the Retreat Cost).

ability.name: Heat Shift
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Heat Rotom's type is Fire until the end of your turn.

attacks.name: Warm Up
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Heat Burn
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

ability.name: Mow Shift
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Mow Rotom's type is Grass until the end of your turn.

attacks.name: Mow Down
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to each of your opponent's Pokémon.

ability.name: Wash Shift
ability.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Wash Rotom's type is Water until the end of your turn.

attacks.name: Cleanse Away
attacks.text: Remove 3 damage counters from each of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Drain Wash
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

name: Charon's Choice
text: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, put this card into your hand instead of discarding it.

Search your deck for any Rotom and switch it with any Rotom you have in play. Any cards attached to Rotom and damage counters on it are now on the new Pokémon. (Remove all Special Conditions and effects from Rotom.) Put Rotom on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.
